1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,760
All characters and events in this series are fictional
and created solely for entertainment purposes.
Viewer discretion is advised.

2
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,640
If Sun isn’t available,

3
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,080
Fey can go instead.

4
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:45,080
It’s already noon. Would you like to grab lunch together?

5
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:45,920
Sure thing.

6
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:49,120
You’ll have to pick me up and drop me off until my car is fixed.

7
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:53,320
If this weren’t about work, I’d understand that you’re just worried about me.

8
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:55,200
Then… could I stay in you room tonight?

9
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:58,680
Doing this will help you relax and ease the tension

10
00:01:59,759 --> 00:02:01,680
I’ve never done it.

11
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:05,440
Then, this is okay for you, right?

12
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:08,800
Then how about we swap the thank-you for a drink with me instead?

13
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:11,920
I thought you said you were going to the wrap party.

14
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:14,320
Then why are you out here dancing and teasing other guys?

15
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:18,079
Next time, keep your disgusting behavior to yourself.

16
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:19,400
Please let me go, P'Flint.

17
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:22,560
If that’s what it takes for you to trust me, then go ahead.

18
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,160
What are you doing?

19
00:02:31,040 --> 00:02:32,040
Why didn’t you answer the phone?

20
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,280
Why didn’t she answer the phone?

21
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,160
What are you doing?

22
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:09,040
Why didn’t you answer the phone?

23
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,040
When you’re not wearing makeup…

24
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:21,480
You actually look like a sweet, well-mannered girl.

25
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:24,120
When you keep ringing other people’s doorbells over and over…

26
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:26,760
That does make you seem a bit rude and no manners, Win.

27
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:57,600
Seriouly!?

28
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:02,760
Dude! Are you going to red carpet or something!?

29
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:07,600
A queen.

30
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,880
Gotta keep the crown too right!.

31
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,400
Queen!?

32
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:15,240
A queen who ditches her friends at a pub?

33
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,920
Let me tell you something.

34
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:22,840
The only queen you could ever be is the Evil Queen.

35
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:27,880
If I really am the Evil Queen like you say…

36
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:30,240
I would’ve killed that woman back at the pub already.

37
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,360
What do you mean by that?

38
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,320
Well, last night there was some crazy woman. I don’t even know who she was…

39
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:40,040
She barged in and kissed me right there in the bathroom.

40
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:43,000
Wait wait. She kissed you!?

41
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:49,800
Damn it, Jan. why didn’t you tell me last night?

42
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,880
What’s wrong with you?

43
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,880
And what could you have done if I’d told you?

44
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,680
I was already kissed.

45
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,680
The thing is, what I’m curious about is…

46
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:03,760
Why did that woman talk like I was her girlfriend?

47
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:07,920
When I’d never even seen her before.

48
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:11,320
I think maybe you just look like someone she knows.

49
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,920
When you went to the bathroom last night, right?

50
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:17,600
Someone asked me if I came with a celebrity.

51
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:22,000
I think she said her name was…

52
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,600
Sun.

53
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,520
Yeah yeah. Sun Atita.

54
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:30,960
At first, I was really confused. Your names even sound kind of similar.

55
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:32,880
Sun.

56
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:35,880
and Jan.

57
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:42,440
Sun Atita...Right?

58
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:48,520
Isn’t what happened last night enough already?

59
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:57,640
Sun, could you talk to me first? Please don’t turn your back on me like this.

60
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:03,960
We were done talking last night.

61
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:14,640
You know it’s not over yet, Sun.

62
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:25,960
What is it that you still want from me, P'Flint?

63
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:37,280
I’ve already given you everything you wanted.

64
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:43,200
If you’re so sure that I’m the one at fault, P'Flint...

65
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:46,120
that I’m a bad woman.

66
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:50,520
Going out, messing around with other people.

67
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,680
So tell me,

68
00:07:56,800 --> 00:08:00,280
what could you possibly want from a woman like me?

69
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,960
I'm sorry

70
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:19,920
I’m sorry for what I said to you.

71
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:28,320
But everything I did

72
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,600
was because I was worried about you, Sun.

73
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:42,039
Worried?

74
00:08:44,159 --> 00:08:48,760
All this time, you never even paid attention to me.

75
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:53,440
You didn’t even know how I felt about you.

76
00:08:57,760 --> 00:09:00,800
But now you’re saying you’re worried about me.

77
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:04,560
I’m not something you can just do whatever you want with, P'Flint.

78
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,760
Jan

79
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,080
Jan

80
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:48,880
Jan

81
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,040
This looks exactly like twins, Jan.

82
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:59,240
The only difference is the makeup you’re wearing.

83
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:02,920
Now I understand why, whenever we went out together…

84
00:11:02,920 --> 00:11:04,480
Everyone was staring.

85
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:07,840
Check this out.

86
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:10,960
There are leaked pictures of you and me.

87
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,720
(Guess who we spotted. Everyone’s internet sweetheart?)

88
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,960
How did I never know about any of this?

89
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:24,360
That’s weird. Since when do you care about Thai celebrities?

90
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,640
Besides,

91
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:28,480
You’re barely ever in Thailand anyway.

92
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:30,000
You’re always flying back and forth.

93
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:34,360
Otherwise, there’d be way more leaked photos by now.

94
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,960
Do you think you could get me this actress’s contact information?

95
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:46,880
Honestly, it wouldn’t be that hard if the situations were normal.

96
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:50,160
But we’re the reason she ended up with a scandal.

97
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,600
I don’t think the agency would ever agree to let us meet her.

98
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:00,680
Wait.

99
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,960
Where are you going?

100
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:06,120
If the company is a dead end,

101
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:08,080
I'll figure my way out!.

102
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,920
Is there anything you feel like eating right now?

103
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,720
I’ll make it for you.

104
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:34,920
It’s okay. I don’t usually eat breakfast.

105
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:07,920
Then today, how about we go…

106
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:10,640
I have an event to attend today.

107
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,840
P'Mooham should be here soon.

108
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:17,840
You can head back whenever it’s convenient for you.

109
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:24,240
I’m not leaving until we finish talking.

110
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:25,760
Let go of me.

111
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:30,240
I know I was wrong.

112
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:37,520
I was wrong for not believing what you said.

113
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:43,160
I was wrong for letting my emotions hurt you.

114
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,720
Even though you never lied to me at all.

115
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:52,520
But if you hate me…

116
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,080
I understand.

117
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:02,600
But I just want to ask you one thing.

118
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:08,240
I want you to believe that,

119
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:12,760
to me, you were never just an object.

120
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,000
You mean so much more than that.

121
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,840
If it weren’t for what happened last night,

122
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:39,080
would I still matter to you, P’Flint?

123
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:02,200
Oh, Sun. I thought you were still asleep.

124
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:06,480
Sun.

125
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:09,760
Weren’t you saying last night that you weren’t in
a hurry to come back to see Khun Rafah?

126
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,760
Good morning. Khun Rafah.

127
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:16,280
You just went to Hong Kong, didn’t you? You’re back pretty quickly.

128
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:18,640
What event is Sun attending today?

129
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:23,440
Oh, today is the launch event for Sun as the new brand presenter.

130
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:26,240
It’s a private event. You don’t have to worry.

131
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:30,200
Is her latest presenter role the one where she’s paired with Khun Nop?

132
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:32,000
Yes.

133
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,760
Let’s go, P’Mooham. I don’t want to arrive late.

134
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:41,200
Please take good care of Sun for me, Khun Mooham.
I’ll come pick her up as soon as I’m done with work.

135
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:48,760
You don’t have to come pick me up, P’Flint. You’re probably busy.

136
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:54,120
P’Mooham is my manager. She’s always taken good care of me.

137
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:58,520
You don’t have to worry, P’Flint. I won’t go do anything inappropriate.

138
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:01,640
Excuse me.

139
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:04,600
Let’s go, P’Mooham.

140
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:30,240
Hello, Khun Sun. There’s a delivery rider downstairs with food for you.

141
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,920
Would you like our staff to bring it up for you, Khun Sun?

142
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:51,720
Do you want something to eat? I can make it for you.

143
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:56,240
It’s okay. I don’t usually eat breakfast.

144
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:57,840
(Even if you never see me, there’s never a day I don’t see you.)

145
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,320
Fey. Where are you?

146
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,320
There’s something I’d like your help with.

147
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:36,040
I can’t even take care of myself right now.

148
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:39,360
What happened this time, P’Flint?

149
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:47,000
I know you want to meet that celebrity.

150
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:49,600
But do we really have to go this far, Jan?

151
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,000
I think the glasses alone should be fine.

152
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:51,920
Enough?

153
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:55,400
I just went to the restroom, and I still had to run away from the fans.

154
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:56,920
This works.

155
00:18:56,920 --> 00:19:00,880
If you want to wear it, just do it yourself. Why am I dragged into this?

156
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:04,920
Weren’t you the one who said you had leaked photos with that celebrity?

157
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:07,440
If we don’t dress like this and someone sees us…

158
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:08,880
It’ll turn into a huge scandal.

159
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,840
I’m asking you for real.

160
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:18,160
You met that star. So what? What did you get?

161
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:20,800
Have you ever heard of the doppelgänger phenomenon?

162
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:25,960
They say every person has seven people in the world who look exactly like them.

163
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:29,080
Even though none of them are related by blood.

164
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:31,880
I think you looking like that celebrity,

165
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:34,480
might just be a coincidence.

166
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:36,240
Coincidence?

167
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:46,160
And what if I told you that this celebrity was born on the same day as me?

168
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:08,360
Hello, Sun Atita.

169
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:13,760
I bought a plane ticket to Thailand just to see you at this event.

170
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:40,360
You’re really standing out with that disguise, P'Flint.

171
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:52,160
I thought you said you were keeping a low profile.

172
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:54,760
I spotted you the moment you walked in.

173
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:57,320
What took you so long, Fey?

174
00:20:57,320 --> 00:20:59,320
I called you two hours ago.

175
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:03,680
Umm.

176
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,640
Hello Khun Rafah.

177
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:13,920
Why are you two here together?

178
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:18,120
All you have are questions, no concern for me at all.

179
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:21,120
The reason we came together is that I crashed into her car.

180
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:24,080
It was the day she invited us to dinner.

181
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,640
She didn’t have a car, so she asked me to…

182
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:31,480
I’ve been picking him up and dropping him off,
it’s just taking responsibility as the other party.

183
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,520
Don’t you remember, P'Flint?

184
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:41,920
Actually, our company has plenty of cars.

185
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:45,240
If there’s a car you like, you’re welcome to choose one and use it.

186
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:49,960
It’s okay. I’m just not comfortable using someone else’s car.

187
00:21:50,360 --> 00:21:52,360
I’m more comfortable driving my own car.

188
00:21:58,120 --> 00:21:58,760
Khun Sun.

189
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:00,400
Khun Sun.

190
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:22,440
Beautiful, isn’t it?

191
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:28,200
And this is the gift I prepared for you.

192
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:32,160
Sun Atita. Sun Atita.

193
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:37,680
I waited here because I want to give this for you.

194
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:39,280
I hope you like the gifts.

195
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:43,080
Thank you for coming all this way to see me and for bringing me a gift.

196
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:45,240
I’ll take good care of it.

197
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:47,440
You’re such a lovely fan.

198
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:49,280
And I love you too.

199
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:50,760
I love you.

200
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,400
Good luck.

201
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:55,880
Good luck.

202
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:19,560
Sun, the fans are watching.

203
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:42,800
I think this one’s just as scary as a sasaeng.

204
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:51,760
You can go ahead and take photos. Feel free to take as many as you like.

205
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:00,200
Sun's here.

206
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:20,320
You’re already inside?

207
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:22,680
You could’ve told me first.

208
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:25,720
Just wait at the shop. I’ll call you as soon as I’m done.

209
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:29,880
Then you could’ve just had me wait in the car.
There was no need to make me get dressed.

210
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:31,360
On top of that, it’s hot.

211
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:32,840
You sound like an old person.

212
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:35,880
Hello.

213
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:07,840
May I take a photo? Please get ready.

214
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:12,560
Thank you, everyone.

215
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:16,240
Wait a moment. There’s a joint interview as well. Please come over for the interview.

216
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:18,960
- Sure.
- Okay.

217
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:22,120
Excuse us, we’re going to clear the area.

218
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:24,200
Why is there a joint interview, P’Mooham?

219
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:27,040
Uh… the network just issued an order, Sun.

220
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:31,280
I just found out myself. Let’s go with the flow for now, okay?

221
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,960
Okay. You’ve got this, Sun.

222
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:39,280
Okay, is everyone ready?

223
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:41,440
Hello, Nong Nop and Nong Sun.

224
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:45,960
Regarding the leaked photos of the two of you going up to the condo, and the images reported in the news. Could you tell us what really happened?

225
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:50,360
Honestly, I was quite shocked when I first saw the news.

226
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:54,440
But just as P'Nop mentioned in his previous interview,
there were actually many of us there that day.

227
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:57,760
It wasn’t just P'Nop and me, like it appeared in the news.

228
00:25:58,120 --> 00:26:00,920
Actually, the others who were there that day were even joking about it, saying,

229
00:26:01,120 --> 00:26:04,080
‘Why was the photographer so mean? None of us showed up in the photos at all.’

230
00:26:06,520 --> 00:26:09,440
As for the leaked photos taken at the club, I’ve seen them myself,

231
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:12,640
and I want to clearly state here that it is definitely not Sun.

232
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:15,000
Because both the outfit and the location,

233
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:16,840
There’s absolutely no way it could be Sun.

234
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:19,200
Sun would never dress like that.

235
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:22,640
And most importantly, Sun doesn’t drink alcohol.

236
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:26,600
Isn't it?

237
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:30,120
Yes.

238
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:34,160
That photo is really not me, just as he has already said.

239
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:40,280
You seem to know each other so well
should we turn this from a shipped couple into a real one?

240
00:26:44,840 --> 00:26:48,400
As for the two of us, if everyone sees us as more than just a shipped couple…

241
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:52,680
I’m happy, because it means everyone is really into our chemistry.

242
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:56,320
The two of us always put our hearts into every project, for our lovely fans.

243
00:26:56,320 --> 00:26:59,600
Please look forward to our upcoming drama that will air soon.

244
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:04,040
Please support it, everyone. I guarantee you’ll fall in love with Sun just like I did.

245
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:10,120
I mean, I’m talking about the character.

246
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:12,480
Ah...

247
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:15,600
Looks like someone’s getting flustered.

248
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:19,480
What do you mean? Was it really that obvious?

249
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:24,600
With moments like this,
it’s definitely going to be all over everyone’s feed for the next three days.

250
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:27,760
Looks like I’ve got some new competition.

251
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:30,440
And who told you to compete?

252
00:27:31,320 --> 00:27:34,040
Why? Are you jealous, Fey?

253
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:36,680
You’re so full of yourself.

254
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:47,000
Does it smell nice? it's really nice. nice and wafty.

255
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:54,920
Where are you going?

256
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:05,320
Excuse me.

257
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:18,800
Everyone, Sun may need to step aside and stand by for a moment.

258
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:21,200
I’ll need to take Sun with me for a moment.

259
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:23,000
Thank you. Everyone.

260
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:26,400
Okay, Nop, please continue.

261
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:28,680
Nop.

262
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:54,640
Are you okay?

263
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,000
Sorry.

264
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:01,720
Are you okay?

265
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:12,160
Excuse me. Excuse me.

266
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:17,240
Let's go.

267
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:21,760
Win, can you bring the car to pick me up at the venue right now?

268
00:29:34,120 --> 00:29:35,360
Where did she go?

269
00:29:57,760 --> 00:29:59,280
What's up, Fey?

270
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:03,760
(Only I see your light)

271
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:06,600
(Only I see your light)
- Earlier, before entering the event, someone gave this to Sun.

272
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:12,080
Should we contact the police about this?

273
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:18,080
Some types of sasaeng fans just want attention from the artist.

274
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:21,880
They don’t really care whether that attention is appropriate or not.

275
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:26,560
If we report it to the police,
it might only fuel their desire for attention and make them even happier.

276
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:31,120
This could actually put Sun in even more danger than before.

277
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:37,520
So what should we do in this situation, P’Flint?

278
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:56,200
What is it with today? Everything keeps going wrong.

279
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:59,920
With the interview with Nop and the whole sasaeng fan thing…

280
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:02,880
I’m getting a terrible headache from all this.

281
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:05,800
Sun.

282
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:08,560
Are you okay?

283
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:13,080
If you’re still scared about the sasaeng fan,
do you want me to stay over with you tonight?

284
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:17,440
It’s okay, P’Mooham. I’m probably just a bit tired.

285
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:22,040
If anything happens, you have to tell me, okay? You know I’m worried about you.

286
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:25,080
Then should I stay and take care of you?

287
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:29,880
My condo is already pretty close to yours.

288
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:32,560
I think it might be more convenient if I do it than P’Mooham.

289
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:36,320
How did you know where Sun’s condo is?

290
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:46,200
Khun Sun, Khun Rafah asked me to escort you.

291
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:04,520
It’s okay. I’ll open it myself.

292
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:07,480
Let’s go home.

293
00:33:01,960 --> 00:33:03,960
Are you okay?

294
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:19,000
(Certificate of Name Change Registration)

295
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:28,680
Win.

296
00:33:34,800 --> 00:33:36,560
Sun Atita...

297
00:33:38,040 --> 00:33:39,960
She’s my twin.

298
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:41,000
Huh!?

299
00:33:56,560 --> 00:33:58,560
Alright. I’ll head in today.

300
00:33:59,280 --> 00:34:00,720
Tell the staff to get the car ready.

301
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:08,120
Your car’s ready. I’ll take you to pick it up today.

302
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:10,679
That was fast.

303
00:34:11,120 --> 00:34:12,840
Our company works fast.

304
00:34:13,080 --> 00:34:16,320
Isn’t that a good thing? I thought you said you don’t like driving other people’s cars.

305
00:34:16,600 --> 00:34:19,159
I don’t like driving for other people either.

306
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:48,040
Almost got yourself another accident, didn’t you?

307
00:34:53,560 --> 00:34:55,880
The car came out of nowhere. How was I supposed to see it?

308
00:34:56,920 --> 00:35:00,480
Hurry and get in the car, so I can take you to pick up your car and get this over with.

309
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:02,400
So we can be done with this.

310
00:35:02,880 --> 00:35:03,800
Hold on.

311
00:35:05,080 --> 00:35:07,240
Before we go, can we get something to eat first?

312
00:35:07,240 --> 00:35:08,720
We haven't eaten anything yet.

313
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:10,880
Aren't you hungry?

314
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:20,080
I'm not hungry.

315
00:35:25,560 --> 00:35:28,560
Wow, You're not even hungry huh?

316
00:35:29,480 --> 00:35:33,000
You should eat something first. At this rate, you’ll run out of energy to complain.

317
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:34,240
Not your business.

318
00:35:43,760 --> 00:35:46,480
(Obsessive to the point of harassment:
exposing sasaeng behavior behind attacks on artists)

319
00:35:51,720 --> 00:35:52,560
Here.

320
00:35:54,680 --> 00:35:55,920
Thank you.

321
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:10,120
You still haven’t eaten? Your stomach’s going to start growling again.

322
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:15,120
If I’m eating, it has to be delicious.

323
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:20,040
Actually, you have to wait a full five minutes for the noodles to get soft enough.

324
00:36:22,240 --> 00:36:25,040
If you eat noodles that hard, you’re going to get bloated.

325
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,440
Are you worried about me?

326
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:36,560
You're full of yourself.

327
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:41,240
I mean… are you worried about Sun?

328
00:36:41,680 --> 00:36:43,720
I saw that you were looking up information about sasaeng fans.

329
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:51,360
Of course I’m worried. Sun is my only close friend.

330
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:55,640
Besides, Sun is way too optimistic.

331
00:36:56,040 --> 00:36:57,920
She thinks everyone is a good person.

332
00:36:58,200 --> 00:37:02,280
It makes me worry that she might get taken advantage of… or even get hurt.

333
00:37:04,080 --> 00:37:07,800
You’re acting like Sun’s personal bodyguard.

334
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:09,640
Aren’t you worried about yourself?

335
00:37:12,040 --> 00:37:15,160
Someone like me won’t let anyone hurt me that easily.

336
00:37:36,440 --> 00:37:38,320
I’m pretty easygoing.

337
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:40,360
I thought you’d be into fancy food.

338
00:37:41,840 --> 00:37:44,120
Food is food. It all fills me up anyway.

339
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:47,200
Actually, I kind of prefer this.

340
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:50,720
No formalities. No need to be careful about anything.

341
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:53,600
Even when I eat messily, no one says anything.

342
00:38:09,080 --> 00:38:10,520
Are you okay? Sun?

343
00:38:12,360 --> 00:38:14,360
I feel a little strange.

344
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:18,360
If you’re worried about today, I can have a guard keep watch.

345
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,880
I promise, no one will be able to hurt you.

346
00:38:26,320 --> 00:38:30,360
It feels strange that you went to the event.

347
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:33,360
I remember that…

348
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:36,600
Didn’t I tell you that you didn’t have to go?

349
00:38:47,280 --> 00:38:48,760
But I'm worried about you.

350
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:50,360
In what position?

351
00:38:52,200 --> 00:38:53,840
an acquaintance?

352
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:57,040
a friend of your sister?

353
00:38:58,240 --> 00:39:00,240
or the company’s presenter?

354
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:08,600
Are you still mad at me?

355
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:10,600
Do I even have the right to be mad at you, P'Flint?

356
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:14,560
Sun.

357
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:17,680
Please, do as you like, P'Flint. Excuse me.

358
00:40:01,560 --> 00:40:04,000
You’re not tricking me into getting murdered, are you?

359
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:06,720
If I were going to kill you, I wouldn’t need to trick you into coming here.

360
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:09,600
Please check the car quickly so we can get going.

361
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:20,440
You’ve hugged me twice today.

362
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:28,480
I was just startled. Who suddenly sets off the car alarm like that?

363
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:33,040
Hey, you told me to check, so I did. How was I supposed to know you’d be that jumpy?

364
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:35,520
So, everything’s all set, right?

365
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:40,360
So that means I’ve fully compensated you. I’m no longer your counterpart.

366
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:41,520
Bye.

367
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:49,360
If you’d step aside, please.

368
00:41:01,200 --> 00:41:02,800
I haven’t charged you for the hugs yet.

369
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:37,080
Why didn’t you put it back where it was?

370
00:41:38,600 --> 00:41:42,680
If it’s no longer the same, I don’t see the point in keeping it.

371
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:09,680
So… you know how I feel about you now, right, P'Flint?

372
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:17,320
P'Flint, could you please stop hurting my feelings?

373
00:42:25,440 --> 00:42:27,040
Can you listen to me first, Sun.

374
00:42:30,720 --> 00:42:34,240
It’s not just me who feels that way.

375
00:42:39,120 --> 00:42:43,160
I’m sorry I hurt you.

376
00:42:45,640 --> 00:42:50,040
I’m sorry for causing you so much pain.

377
00:42:53,680 --> 00:42:55,680
But everything I did…

378
00:42:59,080 --> 00:43:01,160
I did it because I love you.

379
00:43:45,840 --> 00:43:48,800
It feels more like falling in love with someone.

380
00:43:51,720 --> 00:43:52,760
Well done.

381
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:58,200
We met just once, and before I realized it, they had already filled my whole heart.

382
00:43:58,520 --> 00:44:01,760
What, you’re in love, Fey? I’m telling Mom.

383
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:05,800
Why would you tell on me? Haven’t you ever fallen in love before, P'Flint?

384
00:44:07,160 --> 00:44:09,400
Maybe you just don’t realize it yet.

385
00:44:10,040 --> 00:44:11,720
So… whose bouquet is this?

386
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:15,800
Or did someone confess their love to you on graduation day?

387
00:44:17,720 --> 00:44:19,720
Oh! Sunflowers!

388
00:44:20,640 --> 00:44:24,720
Flowers that always turn toward the sun. How romantic.

389
00:44:37,040 --> 00:44:38,840
Everything that happened between us

390
00:44:41,080 --> 00:44:43,080
I never did it out of emotion

391
00:44:45,240 --> 00:44:47,240
It wasn’t about trying to win over anyone

392
00:44:49,880 --> 00:44:51,560
I did it

393
00:44:54,080 --> 00:44:55,640
because I truly love you.

394
00:45:10,480 --> 00:45:12,400
Can you be my girlfriend?

395
00:47:41,080 --> 00:47:42,240
Dear, diary.

396
00:47:43,160 --> 00:47:45,280
I’m completely exhausted today.

397
00:47:45,760 --> 00:47:47,880
My schedule is really packed.

398
00:47:48,480 --> 00:47:50,360
There’s no time to rest my mind at all.

399
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:53,760
But… it’s kind of strange.

400
00:47:54,480 --> 00:47:58,760
Every time I feel exhausted, one person’s face always comes to mind.

401
00:47:59,240 --> 00:48:01,680
I don’t know how you’re doing,P'Flint…

402
00:48:02,000 --> 00:48:04,240
but I hope you’re doing well.

403
00:48:13,560 --> 00:48:15,320
You’re better now, right, Sun?

404
00:48:15,320 --> 00:48:17,320
Then let’s go see your secret.

405
00:48:18,240 --> 00:48:20,680
Hello again, sir, ma’am.

406
00:48:20,680 --> 00:48:22,080
Well… I’m Sun, and I...

407
00:48:22,080 --> 00:48:23,480
My girlfriend.

408
00:48:24,120 --> 00:48:26,480
Why don’t we take a family photo?

409
00:48:27,280 --> 00:48:30,840
Sun, this time the clip is pretty clear.

410
00:48:32,200 --> 00:48:34,680
Hello, P’Peach. Thank you so much for coming to help.

411
00:48:34,680 --> 00:48:35,960
It's my pleasure.

412
00:48:39,280 --> 00:48:40,360
Are you okay?

413
00:48:40,360 --> 00:48:42,560
I didn’t expect to see you here, Khun Paabfah.

414
00:48:43,160 --> 00:48:45,520
Shall we get to know each other?

415
00:48:47,560 --> 00:48:49,240
Shouldn’t you ask for Khun Paabfah’s consent first?

416
00:48:49,240 --> 00:48:50,680
Hey! you.

417
00:48:53,720 --> 00:48:55,960
Are you looking for me?
